FORMAT: 1A
HOST: https://api.giphy.com/v1

# Giphy API
Giphy API

## Authentication
This API uses Custom Query Parameter for its authentication.

The parameters that are needed to be sent for this type of authentication are as follows:
+ `api_key`

# Group gifs

## Gifs [/gifs{?ids}]

### getGifsById [GET]
A multiget version of the get GIF by ID endpoint.
+ Parameters
    + ids (string, optional)

        Filters results by specified GIF IDs, separated by commas.


+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Gifs Response)



+ Response 400 

        Your request was formatted incorrectly or missing required parameters.




+ Response 403 

        You weren't authorized to make your request; most likely this indicates an issue with your API Key.




+ Response 404 

        The particular GIF you are requesting was not found. This occurs, for example, if you request a GIF by an id that does not exist.




+ Response 429 

        Your API Key is making too many requests. Read about [requesting a Production Key](https://developers.giphy.com/docs/#access) to upgrade your API Key rate limits.





## Gifs Random [/gifs/random{?tag,rating}]

### randomGif [GET]
Returns a random GIF, limited by tag. Excluding the tag parameter will return a random GIF from the GIPHY catalog.
+ Parameters
    + tag (string, optional)

        Filters results by specified tag.

    + rating (string, optional)

        Filters results by specified rating.


+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Gifs Random Response)



+ Response 400 

        Your request was formatted incorrectly or missing required parameters.




+ Response 403 

        You weren't authorized to make your request; most likely this indicates an issue with your API Key.




+ Response 404 

        The particular GIF you are requesting was not found. This occurs, for example, if you request a GIF by an id that does not exist.




+ Response 429 

        Your API Key is making too many requests. Read about [requesting a Production Key](https://developers.giphy.com/docs/#access) to upgrade your API Key rate limits.





## Gifs Search [/gifs/search{?q,limit,offset,rating,lang}]

### searchGifs [GET]
Search all GIPHY GIFs for a word or phrase. Punctuation will be stripped and ignored.  Use a plus or url encode for phrases. Example paul+rudd, ryan+gosling or american+psycho.
+ Parameters
    + q (string, required)

        Search query term or prhase.

    + limit (number, optional) -

        The maximum number of records to return.

        + Default: 25
    + offset (number, optional) -

        An optional results offset.

        + Default: 0
    + rating (string, optional)

        Filters results by specified rating.

    + lang (string, optional)

        Specify default language for regional content; use a 2-letter ISO 639-1 language code.


+ Response 200 (application/json)

        Search results

    + Attributes (Gifs Search Response)



+ Response 400 

        Your request was formatted incorrectly or missing required parameters.




+ Response 403 

        You weren't authorized to make your request; most likely this indicates an issue with your API Key.




+ Response 404 

        The particular GIF you are requesting was not found. This occurs, for example, if you request a GIF by an id that does not exist.




+ Response 429 

        Your API Key is making too many requests. Read about [requesting a Production Key](https://developers.giphy.com/docs/#access) to upgrade your API Key rate limits.





## Gifs Translate [/gifs/translate{?s}]

### translateGif [GET]
The translate API draws on search, but uses the GIPHY `special sauce` to handle translating from one vocabulary to another. In this case, words and phrases to GIF
+ Parameters
    + s (string, required)

        Search term.


+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Gifs Translate Response)



+ Response 400 

        Your request was formatted incorrectly or missing required parameters.




+ Response 403 

        You weren't authorized to make your request; most likely this indicates an issue with your API Key.




+ Response 404 

        The particular GIF you are requesting was not found. This occurs, for example, if you request a GIF by an id that does not exist.




+ Response 429 

        Your API Key is making too many requests. Read about [requesting a Production Key](https://developers.giphy.com/docs/#access) to upgrade your API Key rate limits.





## Gifs Trending [/gifs/trending{?limit,offset,rating}]

### trendingGifs [GET]
Fetch GIFs currently trending online. Hand curated by the GIPHY editorial team.  The data returned mirrors the GIFs showcased on the GIPHY homepage. Returns 25 results by default.
+ Parameters
    + limit (number, optional) -

        The maximum number of records to return.

        + Default: 25
        + Sample: 25
    + offset (number, optional) -

        An optional results offset.

        + Default: 0
        + Sample: 0
    + rating (string, optional)

        Filters results by specified rating.


+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Gifs Trending Response)



+ Response 400 

        Your request was formatted incorrectly or missing required parameters.




+ Response 403 

        You weren't authorized to make your request; most likely this indicates an issue with your API Key.




+ Response 404 

        The particular GIF you are requesting was not found. This occurs, for example, if you request a GIF by an id that does not exist.




+ Response 429 

        Your API Key is making too many requests. Read about [requesting a Production Key](https://developers.giphy.com/docs/#access) to upgrade your API Key rate limits.





## Gifs By GifId [/gifs/{gifId}]

+ Parameters
    + gifId (number, required)

        Filters results by specified GIF ID.


### getGifById [GET]
Returns a GIF given that GIF's unique ID

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Gifs Response1)



+ Response 400 

        Your request was formatted incorrectly or missing required parameters.




+ Response 403 

        You weren't authorized to make your request; most likely this indicates an issue with your API Key.




+ Response 404 

        The particular GIF you are requesting was not found. This occurs, for example, if you request a GIF by an id that does not exist.




+ Response 429 

        Your API Key is making too many requests. Read about [requesting a Production Key](https://developers.giphy.com/docs/#access) to upgrade your API Key rate limits.






