# Data Structures

## Gif (object)


### Properties
+ `bitly_url`: `http://gph.is/1gsWDcL` (string, optional) - The unique bit.ly URL for this GIF
+ `content_url` (string, optional) - Currently unused
+ `create_datetime`: `2013-08-01 12:41:48` (string, optional) - The date this GIF was added to the GIPHY database.
+ `embded_url`: `http://giphy.com/embed/YsTs5ltWtEhnq` (string, optional) - A URL used for embedding this GIF
+ `featured_tags` (array[string], optional) - An array of featured tags for this GIF (Note: Not available when using the Public Beta Key)
+ `id`: `YsTs5ltWtEhnq` (string, optional) - This GIF's unique ID
+ `images` (Images, optional) - An object containing data for various available formats and sizes of this GIF.
+ `import_datetime`: `2013-08-01 12:41:48` (string, optional) - The creation or upload date from this GIF's source.
+ `rating`: `g` (string, optional) - The MPAA-style rating for this content. Examples include Y, G, PG, PG-13 and R
+ `slug`: `confused-flying-YsTs5ltWtEhnq` (string, optional) - The unique slug used in this GIF's URL
+ `source`: `http://www.reddit.com/r/reactiongifs/comments/1xpyaa/superman_goes_to_hollywood/` (string, optional) - The page on which this GIF was found
+ `source_post_url`: `http://cheezburger.com/5282328320` (string, optional) - The URL of the webpage on which this GIF was found.
+ `source_tld`: `cheezburger.com` (string, optional) - The top level domain of the source URL.
+ `tags` (array[string], optional) - An array of tags for this GIF (Note: Not available when using the Public Beta Key)
+ `trending_datetime`: `2013-08-01 12:41:48` (string, optional) - The date on which this gif was marked trending, if applicable.
+ `type` (enum[string], optional) - Type of the gif. By default, this is almost always gif
    + `gif`
+ `update_datetime`: `2013-08-01 12:41:48` (string, optional) - The date on which this GIF was last updated.
+ `url`: `http://giphy.com/gifs/confused-flying-YsTs5ltWtEhnq` (string, optional) - The unique URL for this GIF
+ `user` (User, optional) - The User Object contains information about the user associated with a GIF and URLs to assets such as that user's avatar image, profile, and more.
+ `username`: `JoeCool4000` (string, optional) - The username this GIF is attached to, if applicable


## Image (object)


### Properties
+ `frames`: `15` (string, optional) - The number of frames in this GIF.
+ `height`: `200` (string, optional) - The height of this GIF in pixels.
+ `mp4`: `https://media1.giphy.com/media/cZ7rmKfFYOvYI/giphy.mp4` (string, optional) - The URL for this GIF in .MP4 format.
+ `mp4_size`: `25123` (string, optional) - The size in bytes of the .MP4 file corresponding to this GIF.
+ `size`: `32381` (string, optional) - The size of this GIF in bytes.
+ `url`: `https://media1.giphy.com/media/cZ7rmKfFYOvYI/200.gif` (string, optional) - The publicly-accessible direct URL for this GIF.
+ `webp`: `https://media1.giphy.com/media/cZ7rmKfFYOvYI/giphy.webp` (string, optional) - The URL for this GIF in .webp format.
+ `webp_size`: `12321` (string, optional) - The size in bytes of the .webp file corresponding to this GIF.
+ `width`: `320` (string, optional) - The width of this GIF in pixels.


## Meta (object)
The Meta Object contains basic information regarding the request, whether it was successful, and the response given by the API.  Check `responses` to see a description of types of response codes the API might give you under different cirumstances.

### Properties
+ `msg`: `OK` (string, optional) - HTTP Response Message
+ `response_id`: `57eea03c72381f86e05c35d2` (string, optional) - A unique ID paired with this response from the API.
+ `status`: `200` (number, optional) - HTTP Response Code


## Pagination (object)
The Pagination Object contains information relating to the number of total results available as well as the number of results fetched and their relative positions.

### Properties
+ `count`: `25` (number, optional) - Total number of items returned.
+ `offset`: `75` (number, optional) - Position in pagination.
+ `total_count`: `250` (number, optional) - Total number of items available.


## User (object)
The User Object contains information about the user associated with a GIF and URLs to assets such as that user's avatar image, profile, and more.

### Properties
+ `avatar_url`: `https://media1.giphy.com/avatars/election2016/XwYrZi5H87o6.gif` (string, optional) - The URL for this user's avatar image.
+ `banner_url`: `https://media4.giphy.com/avatars/cheezburger/XkuejOhoGLE6.jpg` (string, optional) - The URL for the banner image that appears atop this user's profile page.
+ `display_name`: `JoeCool4000` (string, optional) - The display name associated with this user (contains formatting the base username might not).
+ `profile_url`: `https://giphy.com/cheezburger/` (string, optional) - The URL for this user's profile.
+ `twitter`: `@joecool4000` (string, optional) - The Twitter username associated with this user, if applicable.
+ `username`: `joecool4000` (string, optional) - The username associated with this user.


